The rooms were nicely decorated, a little noisy, but we ran the fan so we wouldn't hear the neighbors tv.	The rooms are kept clean, and the bedding is comfortable, but the place is showing its age a bit, especially in the restrooms.	The garbage trucks are a little noisy but it is not that big of a deal, it helps you to get your day started a little early.	The hotel rooms do have a pedestrian, motel simplicity that will irk some, but we found our room to be perfectly adequate, the bed very comfy, and we loved the quiet ambience at night, which made for long, deep sleeps.